and then Jason shows up
with a machete

2397
01:44:32,866 --> 01:44:35,494
and basically splits him
in half from the groin down

2398
01:44:35,736 --> 01:44:36,532
through his chest.

2399
01:44:36,770 --> 01:44:40,001
So he splits wide open.

2400
01:44:40,440 --> 01:44:43,307
I mean,
that is horrifically gory

2401
01:44:43,543 --> 01:44:45,977
but it's classic Jason.

2402
01:44:46,413 --> 01:44:48,313
And we did a body cast
of him in pieces.

2403
01:44:48,548 --> 01:44:50,778
They actually, in the house,

2404
01:44:51,018 --> 01:44:55,546
built a Plexiglas floor that the
camera was mounted down inside

2405
01:44:55,789 --> 01:44:56,881
so we could do the shot
through the floor,

2406
01:44:57,324 --> 01:44:58,985
up to the ceiling.

2407
01:44:59,426 --> 01:45:02,554
Then, of course,
there's the next scene

2408
01:45:02,796 --> 01:45:06,288
where Tracie Savage sees Jeffrey
stuffed up in the rafters.

2409
01:45:06,533 --> 01:45:09,297
Even actress Tracie Savage
was unaware

2410
01:45:09,536 --> 01:45:11,663
of just how closely
her on- screen death

2411
01:45:11,905 --> 01:45:14,931
resembled that of a certain
famous, yet ill-fated, character

2412
01:45:15,375 --> 01:45:17,400
from the original
"Friday the 1 3th."

2413
01:45:17,644 --> 01:45:20,272
I had no idea that Kevin Bacon
and I have so much in common.

2414
01:45:20,514 --> 01:45:22,311
Another six degree separation
from Kevin Bacon.

2415
01:45:22,549 --> 01:45:23,379
There you go.

2416
01:45:23,617 --> 01:45:25,050
We died the same way?.

2417
01:45:25,485 --> 01:45:27,612
I was in makeup for 4 hours

2418
01:45:27,854 --> 01:45:29,947
so that they could
glue this torso to my neck.

2419
01:45:30,390 --> 01:45:32,324
Then it was lighting
for another 2-3 hours.

2420
01:45:32,559 --> 01:45:34,959
All for a 3-second shot.

2421
01:45:35,395 --> 01:45:37,522
And you had to get it right

2422
01:45:37,764 --> 01:45:40,392
because then, if you don't,
you gotta do it all over again.

2423
01:45:40,634 --> 01:45:41,601
So we were all kind of
on pins and needles.

2424
01:45:41,835 --> 01:45:43,496
I think that line...

2425
01:45:43,737 --> 01:45:45,364
Chris: We would have
been there already

2426
01:45:45,605 --> 01:45:46,003
if some people didn't have to
go to the bathroom

2427
01:45:46,440 --> 01:45:48,340
every five minutes.

2428
01:45:48,575 --> 01:45:49,667
Debbie: That's what happens
when you're pregnant.

2429
01:45:49,910 --> 01:45:54,074
was put in there just to make
the teenage kids go...ooh.

2430
01:45:54,514 --> 01:45:55,708
and then when I'm killed make
it even more grisly and awful.

2431
01:45:55,949 --> 01:45:58,417
This is a pregnant woman.

2432
01:45:58,652 --> 01:46:00,483
There was never a death scene
filmed for Shelly.

2433
01:46:00,721 --> 01:46:02,086
It was always--that's exactly
how it was in the script.

2434
01:46:02,522 --> 01:46:03,420
I guess you're supposed
to think, well,

2435
01:46:03,657 --> 01:46:04,919
maybe he's joking again?.

2436
01:46:05,359 --> 01:46:07,418
Nice make-up job.

2437
01:46:07,661 --> 01:46:09,959
Although obviously the audience
knows he's not joking

2438
01:46:10,397 --> 01:46:11,728
because they've seen Jason kill
a bunch of people.

2439
01:46:11,965 --> 01:46:13,455
I think I did the first take,

2440
01:46:13,700 --> 01:46:15,361
and I think I heard
some people chuckling.

2441
01:46:15,602 --> 01:46:16,933
They were like -
they were like, 'That's bad.'

2442
01:46:17,371 --> 01:46:19,100
I was like--
that all got into my head.

2443
01:46:19,539 --> 01:46:21,700
It's not the greatest
death scene in the world.

2444
01:46:21,942 --> 01:46:23,534
Well, I don't know
what's going on,

2445
01:46:23,777 --> 01:46:25,039
but I'm gonna go outside
and take a look around.

2446
01:46:25,479 --> 01:46:26,844
I think my favorite kill
was probably

2447
01:46:27,080 --> 01:46:28,547
Rick getting his eye popped out.

2448
01:46:28,782 --> 01:46:30,113
They did change the name
of the character.

2449
01:46:30,550 --> 01:46:32,450
In the original script
it was Derek,

2450
01:46:32,686 --> 01:46:33,846
and the reason
why they changed it

2451
01:46:34,087 --> 01:46:36,578
was at the end of the film
when I go outside,

2452
01:46:36,823 --> 01:46:38,814
and I get killed,

2453
01:46:39,059 --> 01:46:41,994
and she comes out and starts
yelling the name out,

2454
01:46:42,429 --> 01:46:45,057
that they wanted a monosyllabic
name for her to say.

2455
01:46:45,499 --> 01:46:46,830
Rick?.!

2456
01:46:47,067 --> 01:46:48,591
You know, of course,

2457
01:46:48,835 --> 01:46:50,826
the death
that my character experienced,

2458
01:46:51,071 --> 01:46:52,902
me getting my head crushed,

2459
01:46:53,140 --> 01:46:56,667
was I mean, this was, yeah,
that's historic.

2460
01:46:56,910 --> 01:46:59,674
I just remember when
Paul's eyeball popped out,

2461
01:46:59,913 --> 01:47:01,904
the whole audience just screamed
at that one and it was like,

2462
01:47:02,149 --> 01:47:03,639
Oh, that's great.

2463
01:47:03,884 --> 01:47:05,374
Technically,
it was very hard to do,

2464
01:47:05,619 --> 01:47:06,677
and it was one of those things

2465
01:47:06,920 --> 01:47:08,114
you only had one chance
of doing it,

2466
01:47:08,555 --> 01:47:11,718
especially the 3D effect.

2467
01:47:11,958 --> 01:47:15,758
Well, in actuality we did
the Paul Kratka head twice.

2468
01:47:15,996 --> 01:47:18,487
I was actually playing
with a bunch of stuff

2469
01:47:18,732 --> 01:47:20,996
trying to figure out how to make
and collapse the head properly.

2470
01:47:21,435 --> 01:47:23,130
Anytime they wanted to,
we could just pull the string

2471
01:47:23,570 --> 01:47:25,595
and the eye
would pop out of the socket

2472
01:47:25,839 --> 01:47:27,773
and come straight down the line
toward camera.

2473
01:47:28,008 --> 01:47:31,102
The last part of the filming
was basically Jason and Chris.

2474
01:47:31,545 --> 01:47:32,910
(Chris screams)

2475
01:47:33,146 --> 01:47:35,171
And a lot of night shooting.

2476
01:47:35,615 --> 01:47:37,708
She runs up the stairs, and
I'm at the bottom of the stairs

2477
01:47:37,951 --> 01:47:39,612
and she tips the bookcase up
on top of me.

2478
01:47:39,853 --> 01:47:41,844
And I have to say
that hurt like hell.

2479
01:47:42,088 --> 01:47:45,489
It's Dana who finds me
in the closet later on

2480
01:47:45,725 --> 01:47:46,851
with the knife
sticking out of my neck

2481
01:47:47,093 --> 01:47:48,993
after I've already been killed.

2482
01:47:49,229 --> 01:47:50,958
It was an easy day. I didn't
have to memorize any lines.

2483
01:47:51,198 --> 01:47:53,564
When he's breaking down
that door,

2484
01:47:53,800 --> 01:47:55,859
and the whole thing where
he gets stabbed in the hand

2485
01:47:56,102 --> 01:47:57,865
and stabbed in the leg,
those are intense moments.

2486
01:47:58,104 --> 01:48:00,470
I mean, those grip you

2487
01:48:00,707 --> 01:48:04,143
because then it becomes him
not so much a monster

2488
01:48:04,578 --> 01:48:08,605
as a human who has
monstrous capabilities.

2489
01:48:08,849 --> 01:48:09,838
And then I chased her
up the stairs,

2490
01:48:10,083 --> 01:48:11,516
and she went in
through the bedroom window

2491
01:48:11,751 --> 01:48:13,013
and went out the window.

2492
01:48:13,253 --> 01:48:14,777
Then she tried to run away
in the car,

2493
01:48:15,021 --> 01:48:16,147
and the car ran out of gas
on the bridge.

2494
01:48:16,590 --> 01:48:18,217
No!!

2495
01:48:18,658 --> 01:48:20,649
I think I kept in shape
doing that film.

2496
01:48:20,894 --> 01:48:23,021
There were --
there was a time or two

2497
01:48:23,263 --> 01:48:25,128
where I was running
through the woods

2498
01:48:25,565 --> 01:48:27,089
right after the scene
where he grabs me in the van,

2499
01:48:27,534 --> 01:48:29,502
and, you know,
breaks the window with his head,

2500
01:48:29,736 --> 01:48:31,101
and I bolt out the other side.

2501
01:48:31,538 --> 01:48:34,701
There's a place
where I run and fall,

2502
01:48:34,941 --> 01:48:37,535
and actually when I did that,
I didn't get hurt

2503
01:48:37,777 --> 01:48:41,474
but people in the cast--
in the crew were just gasping

2504
01:48:41,715 --> 01:48:42,875
because they thought
I had really fallen

2505
01:48:43,116 --> 01:48:44,743
and smacked my face.

2506
01:48:44,985 --> 01:48:46,782
So that was good.

2507
01:48:47,020 --> 01:48:48,885
When I went into the barn
after her,

2508
01:48:49,122 --> 01:48:52,614
you know, it was--Steve and l
had obviously spoken about it,

2509
01:48:52,859 --> 01:48:56,590
and Jason at this point is now
really angry

2510
01:48:56,830 --> 01:48:58,491
because he hasn't managed to do
what he wanted to do

2511
01:48:58,732 --> 01:48:59,790
and that was kill her.

2512
01:49:00,033 --> 01:49:04,026
And so, he just said, you know,

2513
01:49:04,271 --> 01:49:06,967
we don't need the barn anymore
so just tear it up.

2514
01:49:07,207 --> 01:49:10,108
So I grabbed whatever I could
and smashed whatever I could.

2515
01:49:10,544 --> 01:49:13,104
But then the scene
in the barn on the beam,

2516
01:49:13,547 --> 01:49:15,014
I actually did that
and shimmied out

2517
01:49:15,248 --> 01:49:16,545
and that was,
you know, I don't know,

2518
01:49:16,783 --> 01:49:18,273
20 feet above the ground,

2519
01:49:18,718 --> 01:49:20,083
and I ended up with some bruises
from that one,

2520
01:49:20,320 --> 01:49:22,550
but I turned out okay.

2521
01:49:22,789 --> 01:49:24,654
Jason gets pushed
out of the barn,

2522
01:49:24,891 --> 01:49:26,882
and he's hanging and the mask
has to come off,

2523
01:49:27,127 --> 01:49:29,960
and she sees his face
for the first time

2524
01:49:30,196 --> 01:49:32,994
and recognizes who he is.
- It's you!

2525
01:49:33,233 --> 01:49:35,224
We had a mold
of Richard Brooker's head,

2526
01:49:35,669 --> 01:49:38,900
and we wanted the axe
to be able to stick,

2527
01:49:39,139 --> 01:49:41,266
so that's why we used
the rigid polyfoam

2528
01:49:41,708 --> 01:49:43,005
so the axe had something
to stick into.

2529
01:49:43,243 --> 01:49:46,041
There wasn't that much makeup
until the dream sequence.

2530
01:49:46,279 --> 01:49:48,679
I used to have to go in
and do about 6,

2531
01:49:48,915 --> 01:49:50,940
sometimes 7 hours of makeup.

2532
01:49:51,184 --> 01:49:53,152
And it was 1 1 different
appliances

2533
01:49:53,587 --> 01:49:54,281
that they glued to my face,

2534
01:49:54,721 --> 01:49:56,951
with the one eye lower down,

2535
01:49:57,190 --> 01:49:58,680
you know, and certain teeth
and the whole thing.

2536
01:49:58,925 --> 01:50:00,859
It was awfully painful.

2537
01:50:01,094 --> 01:50:02,891
I mean, he had to be in that
make-up for like 6 hours,

2538
01:50:03,129 --> 01:50:05,029
and it was hot and sweaty.

2539
01:50:05,265 --> 01:50:09,725
And you could see that he
was very uncomfortable.

2540
01:50:09,970 --> 01:50:11,961
The bad part about it was
that as soon as they finished,

2541
01:50:12,205 --> 01:50:15,231
it was usually lunch time,
and I couldn't eat.

2542
01:50:15,675 --> 01:50:17,199
So they used to give me
Tiger's Milk through a straw

2543
01:50:17,644 --> 01:50:19,168
so I would get some nourishment
for the day.

2544
01:50:19,613 --> 01:50:21,706
We shot the ending twice.

2545
01:50:21,948 --> 01:50:24,781
We actually did another ending.

2546
01:50:25,018 --> 01:50:28,010
Dana Kimmell comes up to the
door of the house in a dream,

2547
01:50:28,254 --> 01:50:31,189
and Jason comes through the
front door and decapitates her.

2548
01:50:31,625 --> 01:50:34,253
And that was just
an alternate ending

2549
01:50:34,694 --> 01:50:34,716
that somewhere along the lines
somebody came up with.

2550
01:50:34,928 --> 01:50:37,294
It was a very quick thing.

2551
01:50:37,731 --> 01:50:39,289
It wasn't something that,
you know,

2552
01:50:39,733 --> 01:50:41,030
we knew was going to happen
in advance.

2553
01:50:41,267 --> 01:50:42,928
It was just kind of
one of those added scenes

2554
01:50:43,169 --> 01:50:44,932
that they said let's just
do this real quick.

2555
01:50:45,171 --> 01:50:49,198
It was only when we did
the infamous alternate ending

2556
01:50:49,643 --> 01:50:51,838
that you really started
to see his face

2557
01:50:52,078 --> 01:50:53,340
and that's what
they didn't like,

2558
01:50:53,780 --> 01:50:55,270
and that's why
the alternate ending

2559
01:50:55,715 --> 01:50:57,080
was totally scrapped
out of the movie.

2560
01:50:57,317 --> 01:50:59,945
So we made the mask.
We sculpted it.

2561
01:51:00,186 --> 01:51:03,087
Then they came up with the new
dream sequence

2562
01:51:03,323 --> 01:51:07,817
that Jason's at the house,

2563
01:51:08,061 --> 01:51:09,653
and she sees him
at the top window

2564
01:51:09,896 --> 01:51:11,193
and then comes down and blasts
through the door.

2565
01:51:11,431 --> 01:51:14,889
Steve Miner said that he wanted
this creature

2566
01:51:15,135 --> 01:51:16,102
to come out of the lake as if
it was Mrs. Voorhees

2567
01:51:16,336 --> 01:51:18,304
who had been down there
for awhile.

2568
01:51:18,738 --> 01:51:19,363
I have no idea
how she got her body back,

2569
01:51:19,806 --> 01:51:21,137
but it's a dream.

2570
01:51:21,374 --> 01:51:23,342
They gave us Marilyn Poucher
and just said,

2571
01:51:23,777 --> 01:51:26,746
"She's your guinea pig.
Use her."

2572
01:51:26,980 --> 01:51:28,277
Little did she know
what she was in for.

2573
01:51:28,715 --> 01:51:29,943
Once we started
doing the makeup,

2574
01:51:30,183 --> 01:51:31,810
it took about 6 hours,

2575
01:51:32,052 --> 01:51:32,814
and I remember
just sort of like,

2576
01:51:33,053 --> 01:51:34,281
falling asleep at certain times.

2577
01:51:34,721 --> 01:51:36,689
It was just downright horrible

2578
01:51:36,923 --> 01:51:40,256
because the water was just
full of mosquito larvae

2579
01:51:40,694 --> 01:51:43,322
and baby frogs and tadpoles.

2580
01:51:43,763 --> 01:51:46,129
It was just like--
oh, it was pretty nasty.

2581
01:51:46,366 --> 01:51:49,028
Covered her in river slime
and vinyl worms,

2582
01:51:49,269 --> 01:51:50,395
and the rest is history.

2583
01:51:50,837 --> 01:51:54,933
[Chris screams]

2584
01:51:55,175 --> 01:51:58,110
So this is the actual mask
that was done of my skin.

2585
01:51:58,344 --> 01:52:01,313
It's a little, a little--
oh, here's a worm. (laughs)

2586
01:52:01,748 --> 01:52:02,715
Luckily they were able
to cut it off,

2587
01:52:02,949 --> 01:52:04,712
and we peeled it off

2588
01:52:04,951 --> 01:52:06,043
because then I had to do
the shot three more times.

2589
01:52:06,286 --> 01:52:08,254
While not as deliberately
ambiguous

2590
01:52:08,488 --> 01:52:10,012
as the ending of "Part 2,"

2591
01:52:10,256 --> 01:52:11,314
the film's conclusion suggests

2592
01:52:11,758 --> 01:52:13,089
that the door has again
been left open

2593
01:52:13,326 --> 01:52:15,157
for the return of Jason.

2594
01:52:15,395 --> 01:52:18,228
But what of the fate
of traumatized Chris Higgins

2595
01:52:18,465 --> 01:52:21,127
who was never seen
or heard from again?.

2596
01:52:21,367 --> 01:52:23,699
I would say Chris has recovered.

2597
01:52:23,937 --> 01:52:26,963
Even though she drove away
looking like she was losing it

2598
01:52:27,207 --> 01:52:28,731
there in the back
of the cop car,

2599
01:52:28,975 --> 01:52:30,067
I think
that she was strong enough

2600
01:52:30,310 --> 01:52:34,076
to recover and move on.

2601
01:52:34,314 --> 01:52:37,943
And that's the way I wanted
to portray that character,

2602
01:52:38,184 --> 01:52:40,812
as a survivor,
and I think Chris did that.

2603
01:52:41,054 --> 01:52:43,318
(Screams)

2604
01:52:43,757 --> 01:52:45,384
A new dimension in terror.

2605
01:52:45,825 --> 01:52:48,293
It will scare you!

2606
01:52:48,528 --> 01:52:52,362
"Friday the 1 3th Part 3"
was released on August 1 3, 1 982

2607
01:52:52,799 --> 01:52:54,733
with Paramount spending
millions of dollars

2608
01:52:54,968 --> 01:52:56,458
to equip theaters
with the new technology

2609
01:52:56,903 --> 01:52:58,495
required to show the 3D film.

2610
01:52:58,938 --> 01:53:00,906
Their investment
quickly paid off

2611
01:53:01,141 --> 01:53:03,132
when the film managed

2612
01:53:03,376 --> 01:53:05,105
to knock the year's reigning
box office champion,

2613
01:53:05,345 --> 01:53:09,441
Steven Spielberg's "E.T.,"
from the #1 spot.

2614
01:53:09,883 --> 01:53:13,512
With a final U.S. take
of $36.7 million,

2615
01:53:13,953 --> 01:53:15,944
"Friday the 1 3th Part 3"

2616
01:53:16,189 --> 01:53:19,215
ushered in a new wave
of 3D films in the 1 980s.

2617
01:53:19,459 --> 01:53:22,019
And remains one of the most
profitable installments

2618
01:53:22,262 --> 01:53:23,752
of the franchise.

2619
01:53:23,997 --> 01:53:30,300
I believe the choice to do this
in 3D

2620
01:53:30,537 --> 01:53:32,368
was really risky but,
in retrospect,

2621
01:53:32,806 --> 01:53:34,501
it was brilliant.

2622
01:53:34,941 --> 01:53:38,240
"Friday the 1 3th Part 3"
was the first big hit 3D movie

2623
01:53:38,478 --> 01:53:40,912
of the 80s and the audience
was just screaming.

2624
01:53:41,147 --> 01:53:43,012
And we made our money back

2625
01:53:43,249 --> 01:53:47,015
before the first matinee show
in Los Angeles.

2626
01:53:47,253 --> 01:53:49,847
And I find that very rewarding,

2627
01:53:50,089 --> 01:53:52,557
and it's been great being
able to meet people

2628
01:53:52,992 --> 01:53:54,016
that appreciate
and have enjoyed those films

2629
01:53:54,260 --> 01:53:56,990
from back then.

2630
01:53:57,230 --> 01:53:59,198
Actress Tracie Savage went on
to a successful career

2631
01:53:59,432 --> 01:54:00,558
as a broadcast journalist.

2632
01:54:01,000 --> 01:54:03,230
Best known for her coverage

2633
01:54:03,469 --> 01:54:05,903
of the sensational OJ Simpson
murder trial in 1 995.

2634
01:54:06,139 --> 01:54:08,300
As a news reporter

2635
01:54:08,541 --> 01:54:09,940
in different markets
all across the country,

2636
