see themselves in

2845
02:02:57,837 --> 02:02:59,998
and ultimately sort of
the challenges that he has,

2846
02:03:00,439 --> 02:03:02,407
the kind of outsider kid
who's a little bit freaky.

2847
02:03:02,641 --> 02:03:05,474
He's got hobbies that maybe not
everybody approves of per se.

2848
02:03:05,711 --> 02:03:08,578
At a roadside cemetery,
the gravesite of Mrs. Voorhees,

2849
02:03:08,814 --> 02:03:12,978
and her first name, are revealed
for the first time ever.

2850
02:03:13,419 --> 02:03:15,114
I found out her name
was Pamela,

2851
02:03:15,554 --> 02:03:17,784
I guess about 1 0 years
after I did the film.

2852
02:03:18,023 --> 02:03:19,752
I didn't know.

2853
02:03:19,992 --> 02:03:24,122
Of course we were aware putting
a mother character in the film

2854
02:03:24,563 --> 02:03:29,933
that fans who knew "Part 1 "
would think about that.

2855
02:03:30,169 --> 02:03:33,935
That idea of Joe giving me
a hint

2856
02:03:34,173 --> 02:03:36,539
that maybe
I should look sinister

2857
02:03:36,776 --> 02:03:38,004
when I looked out the window

2858
02:03:38,444 --> 02:03:40,435
because of the mother
being the one

2859
02:03:40,679 --> 02:03:42,044
that did the killing in one of
the other movies.

2860
02:03:42,481 --> 02:03:44,915
Never occurred to me.

2861
02:03:45,151 --> 02:03:46,675
Never occurred to Joe,
I don't think,

2862
02:03:46,919 --> 02:03:48,079
or he certainly didn't
tell me that.

2863
02:03:48,521 --> 02:03:50,386
We didn't play it hard, and we
didn't try to suggest

2864
02:03:50,623 --> 02:03:51,647
that she was going to be
a villain,

2865
02:03:51,891 --> 02:03:53,415
but she does make a judgment
on these kids,

2866
02:03:53,659 --> 02:03:55,991
and it feels like these kids
are going to bring

2867
02:03:56,429 --> 02:03:59,796
trouble and bad stuff
onto my kids.

2868
02:04:00,032 --> 02:04:02,023
And, of course,
she's completely right.

