was hard for Paramount
to ignore.

3588
02:33:46,817 --> 02:33:48,250
What else can you do with it?.

3589
02:33:48,485 --> 02:33:49,816
We've just killed Jason.

3590
02:33:50,254 --> 02:33:51,243
We've just said that
the series is ended.

3591
02:33:51,488 --> 02:33:52,477
You've gotta figure out
something to do.

3592
02:33:52,723 --> 02:33:55,283
So everybody
was trying to figure out

3593
02:33:55,526 --> 02:33:57,721
a way to break the
"you're making the same movie

3594
02:33:57,962 --> 02:33:59,623
over and over again."

3595
02:33:59,863 --> 02:34:02,354
The title of "New Beginning,"
I think came from Frank.

3596
02:34:02,600 --> 02:34:05,398
I think it was how
he was reaching around

3597
02:34:05,636 --> 02:34:06,796
for a way
to let the audience know

3598
02:34:07,238 --> 02:34:10,366
that we were promising them
something new

3599
02:34:10,608 --> 02:34:12,576
after having told them
that it was done.

3600
02:34:12,810 --> 02:34:15,472
I had been an assistant editor
for many years,

3601
02:34:15,713 --> 02:34:19,205
mostly for Michael Kahn who's
Steven Spielberg's editor,

3602
02:34:19,450 --> 02:34:21,782
and I was an assistant editor on
"Raiders of the Lost Ark,"

3603
02:34:22,019 --> 02:34:23,577
"lndiana Jones
and the Temple of Doom,"

3604
02:34:23,821 --> 02:34:26,289
the "Star Wars."

3605
02:34:26,523 --> 02:34:28,252
And Michael said to Frank,
'You should hire Bruce.

3606
02:34:28,492 --> 02:34:29,982
I can vouch for him,

3607
02:34:30,427 --> 02:34:32,292
and if he doesn't do a job
that you like,

3608
02:34:32,529 --> 02:34:33,393
I'll come in, and I'll cut
the film for free.'

3609
02:34:33,631 --> 02:34:35,656
After "Part 4,"
I felt like, okay,

3610
02:34:35,899 --> 02:34:37,924
I need to take a step back,

3611
02:34:38,369 --> 02:34:41,964
and I need to find people
to just sort of have their,

3612
02:34:42,406 --> 02:34:44,966
you know, imprint
go on these films.

3613
02:34:45,409 --> 02:34:45,966
I'll make sure
they come in on budget,

3614
02:34:46,410 --> 02:34:47,809
and I'll make sure
we get people

3615
02:34:48,045 --> 02:34:49,774
that are placed
in the right positions

3616
02:34:50,014 --> 02:34:52,346
so that they're not
going to get screwed with.

3617
02:34:52,583 --> 02:34:54,881
But, you know, that creatively
this is really going to be

3618
02:34:55,319 --> 02:34:55,876
sort of
other people's stuff now.

3619
02:34:56,320 --> 02:34:58,754
With Frank Mancuso, Jr.

3620
02:34:58,989 --> 02:35:02,584
now taking on a more ceremonial
role as an executive producer,

3621
02:35:02,826 --> 02:35:05,294
the job of finding a director
for "Friday the 1 3th Part 5"

3622
02:35:05,529 --> 02:35:07,258
once again fell
to the uncredited

3623
02:35:07,498 --> 02:35:09,762
yet always omnipresent
Phil Scuderi.

3624
02:35:10,000 --> 02:35:12,662
This time, he chose a director

3625
02:35:12,903 --> 02:35:16,930
from the world of
exploitation cinema and porn.

3626
02:35:17,374 --> 02:35:19,035
These guys from Boston

3627
02:35:19,476 --> 02:35:22,604
also did
"Last House on the Left."

3628
02:35:22,846 --> 02:35:25,041
So before the film was finished,

3629
02:35:25,482 --> 02:35:29,418
they were going to Cannes
to sell

3630
02:35:29,653 --> 02:35:30,517
"The Last House
on the Left, Part 2."

3631
02:35:30,754 --> 02:35:33,416
And they offered me
to write it and direct it.

3632
02:35:33,657 --> 02:35:35,818
And I said, Sure.

3633
02:35:36,060 --> 02:35:38,426
Then it turns out that they
didn't have their full ownership

3634
02:35:38,662 --> 02:35:40,596
of the rights.

3635
02:35:40,831 --> 02:35:42,958
Phil Scuderi, he somehow
knew Danny Steinmann.

3636
02:35:43,400 --> 02:35:45,061
And thought
that he would be a good choice

3637
02:35:45,502 --> 02:35:45,968
to direct the film.

3638
02:35:46,403 --> 02:35:49,031
And so, again,

3639
02:35:49,473 --> 02:35:51,338
I wasn't going to be in
a situation where I'm saying,

3640
02:35:51,575 --> 02:35:55,511
"I'm not going to drive the bus,
I'm going to take a step back"

3641
02:35:55,746 --> 02:35:56,940
and then say, "Oh, no,
you can't use this guy,

3642
02:35:57,381 --> 02:35:57,608
and you can't do this,
and you can't do that.

3643
02:35:57,848 --> 02:35:58,815
I wanted to say, "Ok."

3644
02:35:59,049 --> 02:36:00,482
And I knew nothing about

3645
02:36:00,718 --> 02:36:07,556
his past filmmaking experiences
at all.

3646
02:36:07,791 --> 02:36:10,351
He arrived pumped
and full of energy

3647
02:36:10,594 --> 02:36:12,824
and ready to do another draft
of the script,

3648
02:36:13,063 --> 02:36:15,861
which was what everybody
had agreed needed to be done.

3649
02:36:16,100 --> 02:36:17,067
As far as the script
was concerned,

3650
02:36:17,501 --> 02:36:19,628
after they discounted the fact

3651
02:36:19,870 --> 02:36:22,031
that Jason is going to be alive
and kicking,

3652
02:36:22,473 --> 02:36:26,842
they thought that using Tommy
as a new Jason

3653
02:36:27,077 --> 02:36:31,013
would be an interesting
and fun thing to do.

3654
02:36:31,448 --> 02:36:32,745
Did Tommy do this?.
Did he not?.

3655
02:36:32,983 --> 02:36:35,713
Was Tommy crazy?.

3656
02:36:35,953 --> 02:36:38,922
These things were running
through the script.

3657
02:36:39,156 --> 02:36:42,421
Unfortunately, Spielberg
fucked up all our plans

3658
02:36:42,659 --> 02:36:45,890
because he decided he
wanted me in a couple films.

3659
02:36:46,130 --> 02:36:49,497
I was forced,
quite begrudgingly,

3660
02:36:49,733 --> 02:36:51,792
to participate in a little film
called "Goonies"

3661
02:36:52,035 --> 02:36:55,061
and not participate,
as I would have liked,

3662
02:36:55,506 --> 02:36:57,997
in the full version
of "Friday the 1 3th Part 5."

3663
02:36:58,442 --> 02:37:00,603
So instead,
a compromise was reached.

3664
02:37:00,844 --> 02:37:03,005
I would come do a cameo

3665
02:37:03,447 --> 02:37:06,746
to help buy myself
out of the pre-made story

3666
02:37:06,984 --> 02:37:08,144
that we had all come up with
years before.

3667
02:37:08,585 --> 02:37:12,646
To schedule
to get him back was insane.

3668
02:37:12,890 --> 02:37:15,654
He was busier than anybody
I'd ever met in my life.

3669
02:37:15,893 --> 02:37:17,622
So what we did,
we went over to his house,

3670
02:37:17,861 --> 02:37:21,092
and in his backyard
we put up bushes,

3671
02:37:21,532 --> 02:37:23,124
had the rain machine,

3672
02:37:23,567 --> 02:37:26,035
and did it all like in like
an hour and a half, two hours,

3673
02:37:26,470 --> 02:37:29,405
and got him done that way.

3674
02:37:29,640 --> 02:37:31,130
And we used then
a very small woman

3675
02:37:31,575 --> 02:37:33,668
to walk through the woods.

3676
02:37:33,911 --> 02:37:37,074
And I thought it was really
actually brilliantly executed.

3677
02:37:37,514 --> 02:37:40,642
In casting Tommy, uh...

3678
02:37:40,884 --> 02:37:42,749
I wanted someone who was tall,
of course,

3679
02:37:42,986 --> 02:37:44,476
had some weight on him,

3680
02:37:44,721 --> 02:37:47,019
and was good physically.

3681
02:37:47,458 --> 02:37:49,153
When I came in for the audition
I again, I resolved

3682
02:37:49,593 --> 02:37:50,457
I'm not going to talk
to anybody,

3683
02:37:50,694 --> 02:37:51,126
I'm not going to look them
in the eye,

3684
02:37:51,562 --> 02:37:52,893
I'll answer yes or no questions.

3685
02:37:53,130 --> 02:37:54,961
And then when Danny
called me in,

3686
02:37:55,199 --> 02:37:57,565
I just sat down
and looked and stared,

3687
02:37:57,801 --> 02:37:58,631
and I started sweating.
And it was great.

3688
02:37:58,869 --> 02:38:01,667
And he got it.

3689
02:38:01,905 --> 02:38:04,965
So it emboldened me to really
become the character.

3690
02:38:05,209 --> 02:38:07,769
After being released
from a mental asylum,

3691
02:38:08,011 --> 02:38:10,104
Tommy Jarvis is sent to live
in a halfway house

3692
02:38:10,547 --> 02:38:13,209
populated by a group
of at-risk teens.

3693
02:38:13,650 --> 02:38:16,210
Taking a cue from the plot
of the original film,

3694
02:38:16,653 --> 02:38:18,883
the producers decided
that the identity of the killer

3695
02:38:19,122 --> 02:38:21,750
would not be revealed
until the final act.

3696
02:38:21,992 --> 02:38:26,122
"Friday the 1 3th Part 5
would be a whodunit.

3697
02:38:26,563 --> 02:38:30,727
In a sense the whole picture
becomes one giant red herring

3698
02:38:30,968 --> 02:38:34,495
because we're going to
pull the plug on it

3699
02:38:34,738 --> 02:38:36,467
right at the very end
of the film.

3700
02:38:36,707 --> 02:38:38,470
The guys who started the series

3701
02:38:38,709 --> 02:38:41,610
ultimately signed off on that
idea, you know.

3702
02:38:41,845 --> 02:38:42,971
I mean, that was--
that came out of Boston

3703
02:38:43,213 --> 02:38:45,511
and that was okay,
and everybody wanted

3704
02:38:45,749 --> 02:38:48,240
to sort of take this road and
maybe thought it may be cool.

3705
02:38:48,685 --> 02:38:52,553
In 5, I actually played
the imposter of Jason.

3706
02:38:52,789 --> 02:38:55,519
Dick Warlock, who is known
for Michael Myers,

3707
02:38:55,759 --> 02:38:56,817
he was the stunt coordinator.

3708
02:38:57,060 --> 02:38:59,620
Part of that job
was to bring in some guys

3709
02:38:59,863 --> 02:39:00,761
that could play Jason.

3710
02:39:00,998 --> 02:39:03,262
So I brought in three guys

3711
02:39:03,700 --> 02:39:04,132
and when I brought them in,
I knew who I wanted.

3712
02:39:04,568 --> 02:39:06,160
I wanted Tom Morgan.

3713
02:39:06,603 --> 02:39:09,071
This guy's an exceptional
stunt guy.

3714
02:39:09,306 --> 02:39:12,275
He's agile and, you know,
and that's why I wanted him.

3715
02:39:12,709 --> 02:39:13,676
I knew that if Jason had to do
anything at all

3716
02:39:13,911 --> 02:39:15,902
that Tom could carry it off.

3717
02:39:16,146 --> 02:39:19,013
My idea was that I was going
to play the character

3718
02:39:19,249 --> 02:39:21,012
as Jason.

3719
02:39:21,251 --> 02:39:23,048
That's what they wanted.

3720
02:39:23,287 --> 02:39:25,187
And at the end they'd sort out
what the answer was.

3721
02:39:25,622 --> 02:39:28,614
And I did have a couple moments

3722
02:39:28,859 --> 02:39:32,693
where I did play the apparition
of Jason himself.

3723
02:39:32,930 --> 02:39:35,660
In the film, it was obvious
they had to distinguish

3724
02:39:35,899 --> 02:39:38,197
in some way so they used the
blue for the marks on the mask

3725
02:39:38,635 --> 02:39:40,762
for the imposter Jason,

3726
02:39:41,004 --> 02:39:43,063
where when I did
the actual Jason,

3727
02:39:43,307 --> 02:39:46,936
I was wearing the real mask
with the red marks on it.

3728
02:39:47,177 --> 02:39:51,045
There's a shot where the camera
is looking out at Jason

3729
02:39:51,281 --> 02:39:52,748
right as he steps out
from behind a tree.

3730
02:39:52,983 --> 02:39:54,780
I was just standing still.

3731
02:39:55,018 --> 02:39:57,748
I had nothing to do
but to look up at the window.

3732
02:39:57,988 --> 02:40:00,616
I'm in the window upstairs.

3733
02:40:00,857 --> 02:40:02,017
And he was trying
to make me laugh

3734
02:40:02,259 --> 02:40:04,659
standing there in the mask.

3735
02:40:04,895 --> 02:40:06,886
I turned around
and mooned him,

3736
02:40:07,130 --> 02:40:09,325
and he's laughing
underneath the mask

3737
02:40:09,766 --> 02:40:15,671
trying to not do this, you know.

3738
02:40:15,906 --> 02:40:17,339
And I'll never forget
the day we shot that scene

3739
02:40:17,774 --> 02:40:19,571
where I look up
and in the mirror,

3740
02:40:19,810 --> 02:40:21,004
there's a guy with a machete
and a mask on,

3741
02:40:21,244 --> 02:40:22,108
and I look again, and he's gone.

3742
02:40:22,346 --> 02:40:25,179
And is he real?. Is he there?.

3743
02:40:25,616 --> 02:40:27,607
Is he monster or victim?.
Well, he's a little bit of both.

3744
02:40:27,851 --> 02:40:30,251
And I find that when I look
at the man in the mirror

3745
02:40:30,687 --> 02:40:32,018
that there's a monster there
and there's a victim

3746
02:40:32,255 --> 02:40:33,085
depending on which day it is.

3747
02:40:33,323 --> 02:40:35,587
Call me Reggie the Reckless.

3748
02:40:35,826 --> 02:40:38,021
Shavar Ross was--
he was adorable.

3749
02:40:38,261 --> 02:40:41,162
Again, you know,
a little, young talent.

3750
02:40:41,398 --> 02:40:43,992
Yes, Miss Osbourne.

3751
02:40:44,234 --> 02:40:46,702
There was many times on the set
during "Friday the 1 3th Part 5"

3752
02:40:46,937 --> 02:40:48,928
where a lot of screaming,

3753
02:40:49,172 --> 02:40:51,003
and, "Hey, he's got
to get off the set.

3754
02:40:51,241 --> 02:40:52,105
We ain't got too much time.
He's got to go to school."

3755
02:40:52,342 --> 02:40:54,333
Solid.

3756
02:40:54,778 --> 02:40:57,178
In keeping with
"Friday the 1 3th" tradition,

3757
02:40:57,414 --> 02:40:59,644
the services of a smart
and resourceful leading lady

3758
02:40:59,883 --> 02:41:00,872
were required.

3759
02:41:01,118 --> 02:41:03,245
This time, however,

3760
02:41:03,687 --> 02:41:06,656
the film's final girl
was anything but a happy camper.

3761
02:41:06,890 --> 02:41:08,915
John had a very heavy character

3762
02:41:09,159 --> 02:41:11,354
and mine was just dealing

3763
02:41:11,795 --> 02:41:12,887
with trying to do the best
I could

3764
02:41:13,130 --> 02:41:14,927
under bad conditions
because the conditions were bad.

3765
02:41:15,165 --> 02:41:16,860
Low-budget movie making
is tough,

3766
02:41:17,100 --> 02:41:20,399
and it's tough
on kind of everybody.

3767
02:41:20,837 --> 02:41:23,965
She was expecting
to be picked up every day

3768
02:41:24,207 --> 02:41:26,334
and brought to the set

3769
02:41:26,777 --> 02:41:27,300
and, I think, in a limo
or something to that effect,

3770
02:41:27,744 --> 02:41:28,836
and that's another world.

3771
02:41:29,079 --> 02:41:31,013
I don't think
anybody gets above,

3772
02:41:31,248 --> 02:41:32,112
no matter where you are
in the food chain,

3773
02:41:32,349 --> 02:41:36,285
nobody gets above the desire
to do something good,

3774
02:41:36,720 --> 02:41:37,812
but the limitations
of what you're dealing with.

3775
02:41:38,055 --> 02:41:40,023
Danny, you couldn't go to him.

3776
02:41:40,257 --> 02:41:43,693
And actors, especially when
you're young and starting out,

3777
02:41:43,927 --> 02:41:45,895
you kind of look to
the director as a father figure.

3778
02:41:46,129 --> 02:41:48,654
And I had a question, and he'd
just say, "Just do it."

3779
02:41:48,899 --> 02:41:50,332
So from that moment on,

3780
02:41:50,767 --> 02:41:51,859
and that was about, I think,

3781
02:41:52,102 --> 02:41:52,932
the second or third day
of filming.

3782
02:41:53,170 --> 02:41:55,138
So at that moment I said,

3783
02:41:55,372 --> 02:41:56,703
"Okay, you're really
on your own here."

3784
02:41:56,940 --> 02:41:57,872
I'm sure that's
an uncomfortable part to play,

3785
02:41:58,108 --> 02:42:02,135
you know,
when you have a director

3786
02:42:02,379 --> 02:42:06,679
that isn't exactly gracious
but you've got a role to play.

3787
02:42:06,917 --> 02:42:11,320
So I decided to just do
what I set out to do,

3788
02:42:11,755 --> 02:42:13,882
to do the best job I could.

3789
02:42:14,124 --> 02:42:15,250
I understand to some people
that Daniel was kind of coarse.

3790
02:42:15,492 --> 02:42:17,119
And kind of rough.

3791
02:42:17,360 --> 02:42:21,763
I can only say...

3792
02:42:21,998 --> 02:42:23,693
it wasn't that way
when I was around,

3793
02:42:23,934 --> 02:42:25,925
but I wasn't really around
that much.

3794
02:42:26,169 --> 02:42:29,195
In order to maintain the secrecy
of the film's storyline,

3795
02:42:29,439 --> 02:42:31,964
the movie went into production
with a befitting code title:

3796
02:42:32,209 --> 02:42:35,144
"Repetition."

3797
02:42:35,378 --> 02:42:38,905
No way did I know that this was
a "Friday the 1 3th" movie.

3798
02:42:39,149 --> 02:42:41,379
So the first day
we're sitting on the set.

3799
02:42:41,818 --> 02:42:44,844
There's this guy with
a hockey mask and the blade.

3800
02:42:45,088 --> 02:42:48,057
He walks past us, stops
and stares right at us.

3801
02:42:48,291 --> 02:42:50,725
We looked at each other,

3802
02:42:50,961 --> 02:42:53,953
and the whole energy
just turned into excitement.

3803
02:42:54,197 --> 02:42:55,960
We're in "Friday the 1 3th!"
We're in "Friday the 1 3th!"

3804
02:42:56,199 --> 02:42:57,826
I want this looney bin
closed down.

3805
02:42:58,068 --> 02:42:59,968
You tell 'em, Ma!

3806
02:43:00,203 --> 02:43:05,470
I did a fair amount
of ad-libbing as Ethel.

3807
02:43:05,909 --> 02:43:06,375
Horse shit.

3808
02:43:06,810 --> 02:43:07,936
Shut the fuck up.

3809
02:43:08,178 --> 02:43:10,009
You big dildo.

3810
02:43:10,247 --> 02:43:12,511
Lots of swear words came out.

3811
02:43:12,949 --> 02:43:15,110
Who the fuck are you?.
What the fuck do you want?.

3812
02:43:15,352 --> 02:43:18,810
One of my favorite scenes

3813
02:43:19,055 --> 02:43:20,784
is in the kitchen
with a chicken.

3814
02:43:21,024 --> 02:43:24,425
I'm gonna chop you

3815
02:43:24,861 --> 02:43:27,853
into itty bitty little pieces,
my friend.

3816
02:43:28,098 --> 02:43:30,089
You know, the stew that Junior
had to eat in the show,

3817
02:43:30,333 --> 02:43:34,292
it was foul only because
it was cold Campbell's soup.

3818
02:43:34,538 --> 02:43:36,904
Best goddamn stew in the whole
wide world, Momma.

3819
02:43:37,140 --> 02:43:38,869
I thought, you know, we're going
to eat this for lunch.

3820
02:43:39,109 --> 02:43:40,770
Hey, Junior would eat anything!

3821
