03:13:43,912 --> 03:13:47,871
It was probably the first one
that really, to me,

4545
03:13:48,116 --> 03:13:49,743
felt like, "Wow!

4546
03:13:49,985 --> 03:13:53,648
This has turned into
an actual movie.

4547
03:13:53,888 --> 03:13:58,655
Over the years, it's come up
that, you know, I was doing,

4548
03:13:58,893 --> 03:14:01,589
both a horror movie
of "Friday the 1 3th,"

4549
03:14:01,830 --> 03:14:03,798
and also sort of doing
a satirization

4550
03:14:04,032 --> 03:14:06,865
of, not so much the "Friday,"

4551
03:14:07,102 --> 03:14:09,263
but the kind of slasher movies
in general.

4552
03:14:09,704 --> 03:14:11,865
The fact that the characters
reference Jason,

4553
03:14:12,107 --> 03:14:13,836
make jokes about it,

4554
03:14:14,075 --> 03:14:17,169
I enjoyed,
I thought it was a lot of fun.

4555
03:14:17,412 --> 03:14:19,380
Because I've seen
enough horror movies

4556
03:14:19,814 --> 03:14:20,303
to know any weirdo wearing
a mask is never friendly.

4557
03:14:20,749 --> 03:14:22,876
Happy Friday the 1 3th.

4558
03:14:23,118 --> 03:14:24,949
The object of the game
is to find out

4559
03:14:25,186 --> 03:14:28,053
which cabin Jason is in!

4560
03:14:28,289 --> 03:14:29,278
What if it's that guy, Jason?.

4561
03:14:29,724 --> 03:14:31,191
I don't wanna know.

4562
03:14:31,426 --> 03:14:33,018
It was real. Just like on TV!

4563
03:14:33,261 --> 03:14:35,752
I think we're dead meat.

4564
03:14:35,997 --> 03:14:39,160
Sowhat were you gonna be
when you grew up?.

4565
03:14:39,401 --> 03:14:42,996
Some folks have
a strange idea of entertainment.

4566
03:14:43,238 --> 03:14:45,706
It was a way of really
kind of having fun

4567
03:14:45,940 --> 03:14:47,965
and involving the fans.

4568
03:14:48,209 --> 03:14:50,700
Tommy's very bizarre
sense of humor

4569
03:14:50,945 --> 03:14:53,004
really shines through, I think.

4570
03:14:53,248 --> 03:14:55,682
But, yet, a fondness.

4571
03:14:55,917 --> 03:14:57,851
You know I found out
years later,

4572
03:14:58,086 --> 03:15:01,021
meeting Kevin Williamson,

4573
03:15:01,256 --> 03:15:05,022
that that did have an influence
on him for "Scream."

4574
03:15:05,260 --> 03:15:07,888
Killer: Name the killer
in "Friday the 1 3th."

4575
03:15:08,129 --> 03:15:10,791
Casey: Jason! Jason! Jason!

4576
03:15:11,032 --> 03:15:13,967
Everyone was, you know,
very fun and wholesome kids,

4577
03:15:14,202 --> 03:15:15,760
you know, innocent.

4578
03:15:16,004 --> 03:15:18,131
For the roles of likeable
camp leaders Darren and Lizbeth,

4579
03:15:18,373 --> 03:15:20,705
McLoughlin cast his wife Nancy

4580
03:15:20,942 --> 03:15:23,410
and a young actor who would
find out-of-this-world success

4581
03:15:23,845 --> 03:15:25,870
after his brief encounter
with Jason.

4582
03:15:26,114 --> 03:15:27,843
The big discovery of the movie
was Tony Goldwyn.

4583
03:15:28,083 --> 03:15:30,677
"Ghost."

4584
03:15:30,919 --> 03:15:35,856
He became famous
for the movie "Ghost."

4585
03:15:36,091 --> 03:15:38,184
The thing that Tommy brought him
back to life with

4586
03:15:38,426 --> 03:15:41,020
is this spear that he yanked
off of a fence.

4587
03:15:41,262 --> 03:15:44,129
So once Jason had that,

4588
03:15:44,365 --> 03:15:48,927
he had something to spear both
Tony Goldwyn and Nancy with.

4589
03:15:49,170 --> 03:15:51,900
(Screams)

4590
03:15:52,140 --> 03:15:56,042
My wife Nancy had a pretty
close call in the movie,

4591
03:15:56,277 --> 03:15:59,804
and it was completely
unintended.

4592
03:16:00,048 --> 03:16:02,073
She actually almost got impaled
because of the windshield.

4593
03:16:02,317 --> 03:16:06,014
It changed the trajectory
of the spear

4594
03:16:06,254 --> 03:16:08,484
that Jason was lunging
through the windshield.

4595
03:16:08,923 --> 03:16:11,915
I would have been speared,
and it missed me by a speck.

4596
03:16:12,160 --> 03:16:12,956
I mean they could
only do it once.

4597
03:16:13,194 --> 03:16:16,027
It was really scary.

4598
03:16:16,264 --> 03:16:18,357
And then there was obviously
the times

4599
03:16:18,800 --> 03:16:19,391
where somebody
tries to reason with him.

4600
03:16:19,834 --> 03:16:22,894
Please! Take anything!

4601
03:16:23,138 --> 03:16:24,105
You know,
as Nancy does in her scene,

4602
03:16:24,339 --> 03:16:25,772
tries to offer him,

4603
03:16:26,007 --> 03:16:30,774
money and credit cards
and stuff.

4604
03:16:31,012 --> 03:16:33,071
My head was submerged,
literally in the mud,

4605
03:16:33,314 --> 03:16:34,372
Iiterally with a vice.

4606
03:16:34,816 --> 03:16:36,340
And they gave me a regulator

4607
03:16:36,785 --> 03:16:38,218
thinking that would
keep me well.

4608
03:16:38,453 --> 03:16:40,921
Well, apparently regulators
don't work in the mud,

4609
03:16:41,156 --> 03:16:42,783
so the mud's creeping down
my throat.

4610
03:16:43,024 --> 03:16:44,753
The American Express card

4611
03:16:44,993 --> 03:16:46,460
was another thing that I knew

4612
03:16:46,895 --> 03:16:48,954
the way audiences
responded in those days,

4613
03:16:49,197 --> 03:16:51,290
that when that card floated,

4614
03:16:51,533 --> 03:16:53,023
there would always be some joker
in the back of the theatre

4615
03:16:53,268 --> 03:16:55,168
that would go,
"Don't leave home without it!"

4616
03:16:55,403 --> 03:16:57,132
And everybody would laugh.

4617
03:16:57,372 --> 03:16:59,306
They say that there's
always a reason

4618
03:16:59,541 --> 03:17:00,405
that Jason kills someone.

4619
03:17:00,842 --> 03:17:02,867
What did I do?.

4620
03:17:03,111 --> 03:17:05,409
I mean, I was driving.
I wasn't having sex.

4621
03:17:05,847 --> 03:17:07,781
I mean, I was with a guy but we
were doing nothing,

4622
03:17:08,016 --> 03:17:09,881
so it's curious
as to why we were killed.

4623
03:17:10,118 --> 03:17:10,413
I've never figured
that one out.

4624
03:17:10,852 --> 03:17:12,877
Jason has no bias.

4625
03:17:13,121 --> 03:17:15,385
If you were in his territory,
fair game.

4626
03:17:15,824 --> 03:17:17,485
To establish a new look
for Crystal Lake--

4627
03:17:17,926 --> 03:17:21,020
now rechristened Forest Green--

4628
03:17:21,262 --> 03:17:25,221
McLoughlin took his cast
and crew to rural Georgia,

4629
03:17:25,466 --> 03:17:28,799
where they soon discovered
some interesting local pastimes.

4630
03:17:29,037 --> 03:17:32,200
The big thing for the kids to
do on Friday nights

4631
03:17:32,440 --> 03:17:35,375
was a big parking lot,

4632
03:17:35,610 --> 03:17:37,407
and they would just drive
around in this circle

4633
03:17:37,846 --> 03:17:39,575
and drive this loop,

4634
03:17:40,014 --> 03:17:41,379
and that was the big thing
to do at night.

4635
03:17:41,616 --> 03:17:43,846
But it was kind of remote
and sort of out of it,

4636
03:17:44,085 --> 03:17:47,145
kind of not cozy,
for lack of a better word.

4637
03:17:47,388 --> 03:17:49,049
The camp we shot at,
Daniel Morgan,

4638
03:17:49,290 --> 03:17:53,192
actually was the site also of
the movies

4639
03:17:53,428 --> 03:17:54,156
"Little Darlings,"
and "Poiison lvy."

4640
03:17:54,395 --> 03:17:56,158
6 was a lot more fun to do
than 5.

4641
03:17:56,397 --> 03:17:59,093
I think everybody else
was happy.

4642
03:17:59,334 --> 03:18:00,528
You had Tom McLoughlin,
who I think is a real director.

4643
03:18:00,969 --> 03:18:03,437
It really was like a family.

4644
03:18:03,872 --> 03:18:06,363
When you film something
on location,

4645
03:18:06,608 --> 03:18:09,168
you tend to get to know
the cast and crew a lot better

4646
03:18:09,410 --> 03:18:11,503
than you would if you
were filming at a movie studio

4647
03:18:11,946 --> 03:18:13,379
where you get to go home
every night.

4648
03:18:13,615 --> 03:18:16,243
It's not love, it's location
because everybody...

4649
03:18:16,484 --> 03:18:20,284
I was the den mother, and they'd
come with these huge crushes.

4650
03:18:20,521 --> 03:18:23,115
She was great.
She took care of everybody.

4651
03:18:23,358 --> 03:18:25,349
She was mothering everyone
from the beginning.

4652
03:18:25,593 --> 03:18:28,494
Absolutely. I'm glad
she survived the movie.

4653
03:18:28,930 --> 03:18:31,023
because that spear could have
gone right through her.

4654
03:18:31,266 --> 03:18:33,166
By a speck!

4655
03:18:33,401 --> 03:18:34,993
I just had such fun.

4656
03:18:35,236 --> 03:18:36,430
I mean, it's like
a big improvisation.

4657
03:18:36,671 --> 03:18:39,299
With Tom's words.

4658
03:18:39,540 --> 03:18:42,976
He was filming a film
that took place in a camp,

4659
03:18:43,211 --> 03:18:45,873
and it was like he was running
a camp for wayward actors.

4660
03:18:46,114 --> 03:18:49,083
Despite the congenial,
family-like atmosphere,

4661
03:18:49,317 --> 03:18:51,547
not everyone supported the
director's artistic aspirations

4662
03:18:51,986 --> 03:18:53,510
for the film.

4663
03:18:53,955 --> 03:18:56,082
There was a man who, Don Behrns,

4664
03:18:56,324 --> 03:18:59,293
who was a little on the
cheap side.

4665
03:18:59,527 --> 03:19:01,461
The first horror film
I ever worked on

4666
03:19:01,696 --> 03:19:04,130
was "Halloween 1,"

4667
03:19:04,365 --> 03:19:06,458
which nobody ever knew
was going to be

4668
03:19:06,701 --> 03:19:08,601
the big success that it was.

4669
03:19:09,037 --> 03:19:11,938
He, you know, certainly
had a past with doing, you know,

4670
03:19:12,173 --> 03:19:14,937
horror movies and things so he
seemed like the right candidate.

4671
03:19:15,176 --> 03:19:18,168
And, at the time, you know,
he made me very angry

4672
03:19:18,413 --> 03:19:21,109
because as the writer/director,
you know, you had a vision.

4673
03:19:21,349 --> 03:19:23,078
Everything was nickel and
diming, nickel and diming.

4674
03:19:23,318 --> 03:19:24,910
If I wanted a crane shot
for this,

4675
03:19:25,153 --> 03:19:26,120
or I wanted this for this,

4676
03:19:26,354 --> 03:19:28,515
and many times I showed up
on the set,

4677
03:19:28,957 --> 03:19:31,118
and it's like, "Where is it?. "

4678
03:19:31,359 --> 03:19:33,327
It's like, "Oh, yeah.
I forgot to tell you."

4679
03:19:33,561 --> 03:19:36,291
You know I wanted to kill him.

4680
03:19:36,531 --> 03:19:40,058
He said, "By any chance,
you got a deal with Frank,

4681
03:19:40,301 --> 03:19:42,701
do you get a bonus for getting
this picture done on time?. "

4682
03:19:43,137 --> 03:19:44,934
I said, "Yes, I do."

4683
03:19:45,173 --> 03:19:47,198
At the end of the day,
you know,

4684
03:19:47,442 --> 03:19:50,104
every time
you have a restriction,

4685
03:19:50,345 --> 03:19:52,142
you have to come up
with something else.

4686
03:19:52,380 --> 03:19:54,610
And lots of times you come up
with something better.

4687
03:19:55,049 --> 03:19:58,018
By the time cameras rolled
in January 1 986,

4688
03:19:58,252 --> 03:20:00,584
McLoughlin had surrounded
himself with a loyal crew

4689
03:20:01,022 --> 03:20:03,456
and a likeable ensemble cast,

4690
03:20:03,691 --> 03:20:07,286
several of whom were recruited
from his comedy and mime days.

4691
03:20:07,528 --> 03:20:11,055
Tom McLoughlin wanted to
cast experienced actors

4692
03:20:11,299 --> 03:20:13,267
in the first scene
that he shot in this movie

4693
03:20:13,501 --> 03:20:15,731
because he wanted to be
ahead of schedule.

4694
03:20:16,170 --> 03:20:17,501
It was a fairly complicated
scene.

4695
03:20:17,739 --> 03:20:19,104
We were all being beheaded.

4696
03:20:19,340 --> 03:20:22,275
I knew Tom
from the LA Mime Company.

4697
03:20:22,510 --> 03:20:23,477
He was the director
of the LA Mime Company,

4698
03:20:23,711 --> 03:20:25,338
and I was a mime in there.

4699
03:20:25,580 --> 03:20:27,047
And when he was going to do
this film,

4700
03:20:27,281 --> 03:20:28,680
he talked to me.

4701
03:20:29,117 --> 03:20:30,084
"Well, I have a part
I'd like you to do."

4702
03:20:30,318 --> 03:20:31,285
And I said, "Oh, great.
Do I get killed??"'

4703
03:20:31,519 --> 03:20:33,510
He said, "Yes."

4704
03:20:33,755 --> 03:20:35,017
We actually were playing
paintball, and it really hurts.

4705
03:20:35,256 --> 03:20:38,123
After I got off a great shot,

4706
03:20:38,359 --> 03:20:41,522
I made the men put on headbands
that said "Dead."

4707
03:20:41,763 --> 03:20:45,096
Don't be spoilsports.
Put on your headbands.

4708
03:20:45,333 --> 03:20:47,426
(whispering) A foreshadowing
of things to come.

4709
03:20:47,668 --> 03:20:50,034
One of my favorite kills in 6

4710
03:20:50,271 --> 03:20:53,399
was the sort of misogynist guy
with the machete

4711
03:20:53,641 --> 03:20:56,235
who has the machete,
and he's hacking the branches

4712
03:20:56,477 --> 03:20:58,308
and complaining about
women should, you know,

4713
03:20:58,546 --> 03:21:00,104
stay in the kitchen.

4714
03:21:00,348 --> 03:21:03,249
She should've stayed in the
kitchen where she belongs!

4715
03:21:03,484 --> 03:21:05,543
A woman shouldn't
even be allowed in these games!

4716
03:21:05,787 --> 03:21:08,756
And then Jason grabs his arm
and throws him against the tree,

4717
03:21:09,190 --> 03:21:10,782
and he winds up
hitting the tree

4718
03:21:11,225 --> 03:21:13,352
and his head goes back,

4719
03:21:13,594 --> 03:21:17,223
and there's like a bloody
smiley face on the tree,

4720
03:21:17,465 --> 03:21:19,763
and you see Jason holding his
arm that's been severed

4721
03:21:20,201 --> 03:21:21,293
from the rest of his body.

4722
03:21:21,536 --> 03:21:22,662
And then it was a question
of going,

4723
03:21:23,104 --> 03:21:24,765
Okay, you know,
we've seen decapitations,

4724
03:21:25,206 --> 03:21:26,537
you know, how do we take it
one more step?.

4725
03:21:26,774 --> 03:21:29,140
Okay, let's do three in one.

4726
03:21:29,377 --> 03:21:31,504
You know, so that three heads
went at the same time.

4727
03:21:31,746 --> 03:21:34,044
Jim Gill, who now runs
Reel Effects,

4728
03:21:34,282 --> 03:21:36,546
did this really cool gag where

4729
03:21:36,784 --> 03:21:39,412
as the idea was
as we passed the machete

4730
03:21:39,654 --> 03:21:42,817
across the three
artificial dummies,

4731
03:21:43,257 --> 03:21:45,623
a trip mechanism would
perfectly send the heads off

4732
03:21:45,860 --> 03:21:47,191
at the right time.

4733
03:21:47,428 --> 03:21:49,692
It was really authentic,
really excellent.

4734
03:21:50,131 --> 03:21:52,190
Then we made the legs so they
would buckle at the knees

4735
03:21:52,433 --> 03:21:53,297
and collapse out of frame.

4736
03:21:53,534 --> 03:21:55,502
A lot of work went into that.

4737
03:21:55,736 --> 03:21:59,570
And the rating system
made them cut that back.

4738
03:21:59,807 --> 03:22:01,832
The head was so realistic.

4739
03:22:02,276 --> 03:22:06,508
The eyes,
I had more hair at the time.

4740
03:22:06,747 --> 03:22:10,148
It wasn't
until the first screening

4741
03:22:10,384 --> 03:22:13,478
about two minutes
before that scene came on

4742
03:22:13,721 --> 03:22:16,087
and someone on the crew
leaned forward

4743
03:22:16,324 --> 03:22:17,291
and tapped me on the shoulder
and said,

4744
03:22:17,525 --> 03:22:20,551
"By the way, the triple
decapitation has been edited out

4745
03:22:20,795 --> 03:22:21,727
because of the ratings."

4746
03:22:22,163 --> 03:22:23,721
And I'm like, "What??"'

4747
03:22:24,165 --> 03:22:26,292
Just as I turned back to watch
the machete go up,

4748
03:22:26,534 --> 03:22:29,162
and I think you see the bodies
crumple by frame,

4749
03:22:29,403 --> 03:22:31,303
and I remember thinking,
"Wow. What a shame."

4750
03:22:31,539 --> 03:22:34,167
When he fires the paintball
thing to Jason,

4751
03:22:34,408 --> 03:22:36,467
and Jason looks down,

4752
03:22:36,711 --> 03:22:38,679
I thought that was like
really, really funny.

4753
03:22:38,913 --> 03:22:40,710
You see me running away,

4754
03:22:41,149 --> 03:22:43,481
and Jason following me
with the machete, and I'm going,

4755
03:22:43,718 --> 03:22:44,377
"Help, help, help."

4756
03:22:44,619 --> 03:22:45,813
He's gonna kill me!

4757
03:22:46,254 --> 03:22:48,119
And then they cut away,

4758
03:22:48,356 --> 03:22:51,189
and nothing is ever said
about Roy until later.

4759
03:22:51,425 --> 03:22:53,689
"Did you find Roy?. "
And the went, "Yeah."

4760
03:22:53,928 --> 03:22:59,423
And they pull out an arm,
and my glasses and parts of Roy.

4761
03:22:59,667 --> 03:23:01,157
I'll order up some body bags.

4762
03:23:01,402 --> 03:23:04,894
There were the kids

4763
03:23:05,339 --> 03:23:06,328
and then there was
the Sheriff's assistant-- me,

4764
03:23:06,574 --> 03:23:09,168
Deputy Rick Cologne.

4765
03:23:09,410 --> 03:23:12,345
And my mail order laser scope

4766
03:23:12,580 --> 03:23:13,569
which, you know, as you see
where the movie takes place,

4767
03:23:13,814 --> 03:23:15,748
it had to be mail order.

4768
03:23:16,184 --> 03:23:17,276
There was not
a whole lot of places to go

4769
03:23:17,518 --> 03:23:18,280
and buy that kind of thing.

4770
03:23:18,519 --> 03:23:22,353
Wherever the red dot goes...
ya bang!

4771
03:23:22,590 --> 03:23:26,287
Trying to find a cemetery
that would allow us to shoot,

4772
03:23:26,527 --> 03:23:27,858
even though we were calling
the movie Aladdin Sane.

4773
03:23:28,296 --> 03:23:30,491
'Cause that was the whole thing,

4774
03:23:30,731 --> 03:23:32,460
we did not want to say
we were "Friday the 1 3th."

4775
03:23:32,700 --> 03:23:35,430
Old Madison Cemetery,
where we finally got permission,

4776
03:23:35,670 --> 03:23:38,798
and we had one area where we
could drive the truck in there

4777
03:23:39,240 --> 03:23:40,502
90 miles an hour
over the train tracks

4778
03:23:40,741 --> 03:23:41,639
and into there.

4779
03:23:41,876 --> 03:23:43,707
There was an entrance made

4780
03:23:43,945 --> 03:23:46,641
so it looked like the front
of the cemetery.

4781
03:23:46,881 --> 03:23:50,681
And then the rest of it
was staying on the paths

4782
03:23:50,918 --> 03:23:52,818
until the point
where he gets tackled

4783
03:23:53,254 --> 03:23:54,687
and then that was kind of
